 The Special Adviser to the Edo State Governor,  Mr Crusoe Osagie has allayed fears of violence in the coming gubernatorial elections in Edo state, scheduled to take place on September 19, 2020,  saying it will be free, fair and violence-free just like a Christmas Day celebration. In this big interview, Crusoe Osagie told Victor Ogunyinka that 80 per cent of the voters in Edo state will be voting for Governor Godwin Obaseki of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP.  Vanguard News …CSOs protest, petition British High Commissioner over violence …Akoko-Edo monarchs sue for peaceful poll …APC petitions CP over mission of officers in Okpella …Policemen in Okpella, Agenebode, Akoko-Edo doing their job – Osagie …We didn’t deploy any personnel—Police …As Edo Govt denies claim of planned attack By Gabriel Enogholase, Omeiza… August 20, 2020 In "News" Over 50 policemen occupying residence of Obaseki's aide ― APC Policemen in Okpella, Agenebode, Akoko Edo are doing their job ― Osagie As APC petitions CP over mission of officers APC has no reason to fret if they have no sinister plans ― PDP The Edo State Chapter of the… August 19, 2020 In "Edo Decides" The Special Adviser to Edo State Governor on Media and Communication Strategy, Mr Crusoe Osagie, has said that "the candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the September 19 gubernatorial election, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu, former National Chairman of the party, Comrade Adams Oshiomhole and their ilk, will face defeat… July 10, 2020 In "Politics"